The paper deals with automated annotation and content-based image retrieval of medical images using binary descriptors. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of Gabor filters for feature extraction is a common technique in computer vision and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the effects of different parameters on the performance of the proposed method, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL).
